  "_meta": {
    "purpose": "Single source of truth for FDI build accent themes. The skill (fdi-draft-skill) reads this at build time and stamps BOTH artifacts: the walkthrough (build.html) via founder.themeAccent (the 6 `walkthrough` HSL triples), and the dashboard (index.html) via the {{THEME_ACCENT_DARK}} / {{THEME_ACCENT_LIGHT}} placeholders (derived from the `dashDark`/`dashLight` base colors + the fixed alpha ramp below).",
    "hub_contract": "The primary-gtm-team theme dropdown MUST offer only these keys. Unknown key anywhere falls back to 'ember'.",
    "values": "All values are raw HSL triples (no hsl() wrapper): 'H S% L%'. Secondary dashboard colors (--purple/--teal/--q-high/--q-low/--red) are NOT themed - they stay fixed for the tier-legend + info hierarchy.",
    "dashboard_ramp_derivation": "Given dashDark/dashLight {green, greenDark, greenDeep}, the skill emits into {{THEME_ACCENT_DARK}}/{{THEME_ACCENT_LIGHT}}: --green-h:green (RAW triple, no hsl() - hero-glow inner stop + med-chip at their original custom alphas); --green-h2:walkthrough.accDeep (RAW - darker hero-glow OUTER stop; emit in DARK block only, light inherits); --green:hsl(green); --green-dark:hsl(greenDark); --green-deep:hsl(greenDeep); --green-tint:hsl(green / .15 dark|.12 light); --green-tint2:hsl(green / .08 dark|.07 light); --green-ring:hsl(green / .4 dark|.3 light); --green-glow:0 0 0 1px hsl(green / .45 dark|.35 light), 0 0 <22px dark|24px light> hsl(green / .18 dark|.15 light). --q-med/--q-med-d reference var(--green)/var(--green-dark) in the template so they follow the accent (med tier IS the accent, historically amber). --q-high(green)/--q-low(red)/--purple/--teal stay FIXED (tier legend + secondary UI)."
  },
